Description: Papyrus. Seven disassociated small demotic fragments on the rectos (the largest pieces contain only a few words on three lines). Versos: blank.
Cultures/periods: Ptolemaic (The hand of one of the fragments may be earlier than Ptolemaic.)
Curator's comments: Four of the seven fragments contain little more than the occasional sign. Of the three other fragments, two contain personal names.
